title: For Sale/Trade:  EGYPTIAN RASHEED 7.62X39MM SEMI AUTO RIFLE VERY RARE !!!
postcontent: VERY RARE! EGYPTIAN RASHEED 7.62X39MM SEMI AUTO RIFLE. This unique design is a cross between the Hakim rifle (evolved from the Swedish Ljungman) and the Russian SKS. It uses the basic operating system and stock design of the Hakim, but incorporates the exposed barrel, front sight and folding knife bayonet popular with the Soviet Union, as well as use of their 7.62x39mm cartridge. These are believed to have been made circa 1959-60 to provide large numbers of arms using the same ammo as the Russian supplied AK-47s being adopted at that time. This very rare carbine is in great condition.  Wood stock is very nice, with assorted minor handling dings of an issued military arm, but none really significant. Has original 10 round magazine. These were made at "Factory 54" which later became Maadi Military and Civil Industries Corp.  Overall, a very good example of a very scarce rifle, with something like only 6,000-8,000 total production and only about 2,000 brought into the USA. This carbine is a key piece for the “assault rifle” collector or someone interested in Egyptian arms or arms of the Middle East. Priced Reduced:  $700.00
